          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-07 14:09:25" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the light, flames, and heat produced by the burning of materials</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>fire</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though the ancient view of the elements would lead to classification of this occurrence of πῦρ ({S:06100300700000}) as referring to a natural substance, the fact that the reference is to a particular event means that in many languages one must speak of a ‘burning,’ and this must be expressed frequently by a verb or participle rather than by a noun, for example, ‘for destruction by being burned up.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
